    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b.23"/>

                <note type="curatorial">A<del/><add>4</add></note>
                <fw type="curatorial">23</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">TWEEDSMUIR,
                        <lb/>
                        KANAWHA FALLS,
                            <lb/>
                            WEST VIRGINIA</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <salute>My dear Doctor Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It distressed me profoundly to hear of Mrs. Neihardt's transition. You never disappoint your admirers. You accepted this and expressed yourself about it as no one but you would do.</p>
                
                <p>Since a great many people have difficulty expressing themselves except by borrowing generously from you, you are in the minds of many more people than you dream <hi rend="underline">of.</hi> Like so many of the others, I find it difficult, in writing and conversation, to get on without borrowing freely from you. You have not only the admiration of countless thousands of people, but also their love.</p>
                
                <p>The charming young Danish girl often answers a question by quoting one of your poems. The other day when she had done a fine piece of work for me and I commended her, she replied:
                    <lb/>
                    "Lo, I, the witless musican,
                    I have wrought even as the masters
                    of melody,
                    Even as the masters of song."
                </p>
                
                <p>If it is possible for me to think of you more frequently than I have for these many years, I shall be doing so in the days ahead.</p>
                
                <p>Count me and our friend Doctor Vining as among your most constant and ardent admirers. Birgit joins me in affectionate greetings.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Shalom aleichem<add>:</add></salute>
                
                    <signed>William R. Laird!</signed>
                    <signed>William R. Laird</signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Branson</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <dateline>26 July 1958</dateline>
                </closer>
                    
            </div1>
